About Gitology.com
===================

Gitology is a collection of clearly-written guides that teach you how to use Git effectively whether you're a beginner, have some experience, or are an expert. 

The site is a [Sinatra](http://www.sinatrarb.com/)/[HAML](http://haml-lang.com/) app hosted on [Heroku](http://www.heroku.com/). 

About the Author
===================

Brian Tanaka has been in the technical field since 1992. He has
worked for a wide array of companies such as: The WeLL, Silicon
Graphics, Intuit, Nintendo, and RealNetworks. His magazine articles
have appeared in Linux Journal, LinuxWorld.com, and Sys Admin
Magazine. He was technical editor on Practical Firewalls by Terry
William Ogletree, and is the author of Take Control of Permissions
in Leopard.

